## ⚙️ Setup & Installation

### Prerequisites
- Microsoft Power BI Desktop (Free) — [Download here](https://powerbi.microsoft.com/desktop/)
- Microsoft Excel (for dataset viewing)

### Steps

1. Clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/hr-analytics-powerbi-dashboard.git
```

2. Navigate to the project folder:
```bash
cd hr-analytics-powerbi-dashboard
```

3. Open the dashboard:
Open: dashboard/HR_Analytics_Dashboard.pbix

4. If a data source path error appears:
   - Click **Transform Data** → **Data Source Settings**
   - Update the file path to your local `dataset/raw/` folder

5. Click **Refresh** in Power BI Desktop to reload all visuals

6. Use the **Age Group buttons** (18-25, 26-35, 36-45, 46-55, 55+) to filter the entire dashboard
